Advanced Lane Line Finder¶

These are the libraries utilized during this project, in addition to help myself in the understanding of the typical pipeline steps for image processing, I have created a separate file with all the functions utilized, such functions are called here only to pass the arguments. You can find the functions implementations in "Helper_functions_2.py" in this workspace.

4. Image Processing : Color selection, gradients, perspective transform and Polynomial Fit¶

Once I have the undistorted images I feed them into the Pipeline processing function, where the different techniques for color selection, gradient, masking, perspective transform are performed. See images Provided¶
In [10]:
def pipeline(image):
    h,l,s = hf.hls_selector(image)
    color = hf.color_threshold(s, color_t=(170,255))
    sobely = hf.sobel_y(s, thresh_min=40, thresh_max=255)
    sobelx = hf.sobel_x(s, thresh_min=10, thresh_max=100)
    combined = np.zeros_like(sobelx)
    combined = np.dstack(( sobely, color, sobelx))*255
    warped_image, m_inv = hf.perspective_transform(combined)
    return s, color, sobely, sobelx, combined, warped_image

Curvature measurement¶

The measurement of the center of the car and curvature was done using the function Curvature Real Measurement written in the helper functions in this working directory, additionally by leveraging the paradigm of Object oriented Programmin, an object Line was created to store the current position and other values that are attributes of the line, by using these the center of the car was found, as coded in the main pipeline using these lines of code:

In [ ]:
center_car = image.shape[1] // 2
    
    l_c = int(right_pos - left_pos)
    offset = (l_c - center_car) * (3.7/700)

Challenges¶

The changes of light and shadows in the road represent a challenge to the pipeline defined, probably because these ones have an impact in the measurements being taken by the counter of pixels and add noise to the detected lines. A possible way to fix this is implementing a feedback system to control and select what should be the polynomial that should be plotted if the obtained one is above certain threshold
